uences of his theory of the self, arguing that it allows us to better grasp what it means to be ourselves and why self-understanding often involves self-creation. Winner of the Académie Française’s Grand Prix de Philosophie, The Practices of the Self is that rare kind of lucid yet rigorous work that transcends disciplinary boundaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSelf (Philosophy). 0aSelf-knowledge, Theory of. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aselfhood, identity, relationship, relation, systematic, understanding, psychology, belief, desire, commitment, truth, desires, classics, classical, montaigne, stendhal, proust, literature, literary, contemporary, philosophy, philosopher, philosophical, academic, scholarly, research, creation, sartre, faith, sincerity, mimetism, autonomy.1 aBowman, Sharon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022646887740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226468549423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226468549/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles